//Class object and methods real time example

1. ANIMAL(class) - objects: Dog, cat, lion etc..
                   methods: eat(), run()....
                   
------

//Class syntax: 

AccessModifier class ClassName{

//body of the class

}

------

//method: used to perform particular task within a class

Syntax:

Access-modifier  return-type  methodName (List of parameters){

//body of method

}

------

//object: instance of class

There arr 5 ways to create objects:
a. using new keyword.
b. using newInstance() method.
c. clone method.
d. deserialization method.
e. factory method.

//2 steps to create object using new keyword: 
1. declaration :   Animal buzo;
2. Instantiation and Initialization:    buzo = new Animal();

writing both in one line will give object creation syntax i.e

Animal buzo = new Animal();









